<p>This post is&nbsp;a second part about the <a title="URL Rewrite Module" href="https://marketplace.sitecore.net/Modules/U/Url_Rewrite.aspx?sc_lang=en" target="_blank">URL Rewrite Module</a> that I&nbsp;described in a previous post&nbsp;<a title="URL Rewrite Module for Sitecore, part 1" href="/post/url-rewrite-module-for-sitecore" target="_blank">URL Rewrite Module for Sitecore, part 1</a>. This post will cover the creation of some useful inbound rules</p>
<h3>Inbound rules&nbsp;creation</h3>
<p>As we&nbsp;mentioned in the previous post, inbound rules allow setting&nbsp;a regular expression to match on the path of a URL that will be handled rewrite module.</p>
<p>For instance, let's create an inbound rule to route the&nbsp;requests that come from the insecure HTTP and use the HTTPS protocol.</p>
<p>1. Create an Inbound Rule</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>2. To match all the requests,&nbsp;use Regular Expressions in the Using field and set the Pattern field with the value&nbsp;<strong>(.*)</strong>.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>3.&nbsp;Now, we have to filter the requests that are not using the HTTPS protocol. For this, we need to create a condition.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>4. To know if the request is missing the HTTPS protocol, use the Condition Input Type <strong>{HTTPS}</strong> and the pattern '<strong>off'</strong> that will check if it is missing.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>5. Now, we need to create an action that will be triggered if the condition is met.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>6. The redirect action should rewrite the URL so it uses the HTTPS protocol instead of HTTP.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>Once, all these items were created and published, Sitecore is going to redirect the HTTP request to HTTPS.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" /></p>
<p>That's it for today.</p>
<p>Until the next post!</p>
